  "text": "DNA Fragmentation Assay. After treatment of interest, floating and attached cells were harvested at the indicated time points. Washed cell pellets were resuspended in cell lysis buffer [10 mmol/L Tris-HCl (pH7.4), 10 mmol/L EDTA (pH 8.0), 0.5% TritonX-100] and incubated for 10 minutes at 4°C. Cell lysates were centrifuged and then Rnase A (0.5 mg/mL) and proteinase K (0.5 mg/mL) were added and incubated for 2 hours at 37°C. DNA was extracted from an equal number of cells and then was precipitated by etomidate and run on a 2% agarose gel as described previously [CITATION_1] . Agarose gels were stained with etomidate and DNA visualized by an UV transilluminater.",
